\fs24 What is a collection view controller (CVC)?\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\qr\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 >> A collection view controller is very similar to a table view controller in that it is a way to easily present information, but they allow you to present items that scroll in both directions instead of a simple scrolling list of cells, like a table view controller. While a table view controller is entirely row-based, the collection view controller has items in groups of sections, it can have multiple dimensions, you can adapt to different heights and widths, and each cell doesn\'92t feel like just a list.
\b \
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
When do you use a table view controller and when a collection view controller?\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\qr\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 >> You use a collection view controller when you want your cells to have all different sizes or have elements that are vastly different from each other in how they are laid out. A table view controller is best used when a scrolling list of similar cells is desired.
\b \
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
