What kinds of interfaces can you build with CVCs that you cannot with TVCs? Under what circumstances are TVCs preferable?\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\qr\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 >> With CVCs you can build interfaces that not only have scrolling lists up and down, but also have them scrolling side to side. They could also have custom scrolling. There is a lot of flexibility and freedom with the type of interfaces you can make with a collection view controller, but if you want simple, clear information presented in a way that people expect and are most used to, the table view controller might be more preferable.
\b \
